fields.title: PRASTUTI-PAPER PRESENTATION
fields.description:
Prastuti-Paper  Presentation

A competition where participants present their research findings or technical ideas on a chosen topic in the form of a slide-based presentation to a panel of judges, showcasing their understanding of the subject matter and ability to communicate complex concepts effectively  to encourage students to explore and present their innovative ideas in various technical fields. 

Theme: Emerging Technologies in Various Engineering Fields

Team : 2 Participants

Entry Fee: ₹100

Judging Criteria: 
Judges evaluate their presentations based on criteria like content, delivery, clarity, and response to questions.

fields.title: PRAKALP (PROJECT EXPO)
fields.description:
Prakalp-Project Exhibition

Project Exhibition is a technical event in which the participants should prepare their project 
at home and they have to bring the project to demonstrate before the judges.
Participants must exhibit their project in the event of TECTRIX 2K25. On 25th
February, 2025.
 
Teams will be given a space to set up their model/design at the venue for exhibition and for judging.

Entry Fee: ₹200

General Rules and Guidelines for competition
• Each team can have maximum of 5 members.
• The competition is open to only for polytechnic students.
• Members should have a valid student ID card of their college.
• A team member can participate in only one project presentation.

Important note:
• Partial outputs are considered.
• All selected participants will receive participation certificate.
• Basic system requirement will be made available to participants as per requirement of project.
• Participants should bring all their requirements to execute their project.
• The decision of the judges shall be treated as final and binding.
• The organizers reserve the rights to change any or all of the above rules as they deem fit

Judging: Key Evaluation Criteria would be
• Innovation
• Design (Compactness and the efficiency of work done)
• Efficiency (Performance of said task)
• Relevance with practical need

Prizes and Benefits:
Exciting cash prizes for top performers
certificates for all participants

fields.title: INNOVATION GALLERY (POSTER PRESENTATION)
fields.description:
Innovation Gallery- POSTER PRESENTATION:
Participants create a poster with text, graphics, charts, and images to concisely explain their topics's key aspects, methodology, results, and conclusions. 
During the presentation time, participants stand by their poster, ready to answer questions from judges and other attendees, facilitating discussion and deeper understanding of their work. 

Theme: Emerging Technologies in Various Engineering Fields

Team : 2 Participants

Entry Fee: ₹100

Judging Criteria: 
Posters are evaluated based on factors like clarity of information, visual design, technical accuracy, presentation skills, and ability to answer questions. 


Entry Fee: ₹100

Judging Criteria:

fields.title: FILM FUSION FACE (SHORT FILM)
fields.description:
Film Fusion Face-Message oriented Short film

we present the “Film Fusion Face” Short Film Making competition. Unleash your storytelling skills and captivate your audience in 3 to 5 minutes.
we invite teams with a maximum of 4  members to create captivating short films. The rewards are impressive 

Entry Fee: 100

Event Details
The challenge is set for Techtrix 2K25 on 24 & 25 th February , 2025. To ensure a level playing field, we have established some rules:

	Your short film must have a total runtime of 3 to 5 minutes, excluding opening and closing credits.
	It should be a message oriented one
	Films can be in Telugu,Hindi, English, or have no dialogue at all.
	Ensure all content, including footage, music, images, and props, is your original work or used with proper permission.
	Unauthorized content will lead to disqualification.
	Animated and documentary films are not allowed.
	Adult or vulgar content will result in immediate disqualification.
	Respect for religious beliefs and feelings is essential.
	The decision of the judges is final and binding.
